You need to define aesthetics.

## Error in `check_required_aesthetics()`:

na.rm removes the observations (rows) where an NA is noted (i.e. missing data).

ggplot(data = penguins, 
       mapping = aes(
         x = bill_length_mm,
         y = bill_depth_mm)
       )+
  geom_point(na.rm = T)

ggplot( data = penguins, 
        mapping = aes(
          x = bill_length_mm, 
          y = bill_depth_mm)
          )+ 
  geom_point(na.rm = T)+ 
  labs(caption = "Data come from the palmerpenguins package.")

  ggplot(aes(x = hwy, y = displ))+ geom_point()

  ggplot(aes(x = hwy, y = displ, color = year))+ geom_point()

  ggplot(aes(x = hwy, y = displ, size = year))+ geom_point()

  ggplot(aes(x = hwy, y = displ, color = year, size = year))+ geom_point()

  ggplot(aes(x = hwy, 
             y = displ, 
             color = year, 
             size = year,
             linewidth = cty)
         )+ 
  geom_point()

    x = year, 
    y = year, 
    color = year,

  geom_point()
